          "settings": {
            "grid-item_image": "shopify://shop_images/Hose-Iconn.png",
            "grid-item_heading": "Manual Hose Fill",
            "grid-item_paragraph": "<p>To fill the pod manually, replace the 4mm barbed connection with the supplied hose adapter and connect a garden hose. A single fill provides up to 48 hours of watering, keeping your plant hydrated even when you’re away.</p>",
            "grid-item_btn-label": "",
            "grid-item_btn-link": ""
          }
        },
        "grid_item_xC4yEj": {
          "type": "grid-item",
          "settings": {
            "grid-item_image": "shopify://shop_images/Irrigation_3df2efc0-0919-4dea-a99e-cb3043a4262f.png",
            "grid-item_heading": "Existing Irrigation System",
            "grid-item_paragraph": "<p>For irrigation lines, use the supplied line punch to make a hole, insert the barbed connector and micro tubing, and connect it to the pod’s 4mm barb. The pod then refills whenever you run your irrigation system.</p>",
            "grid-item_btn-label": "",
            "grid-item_btn-link": ""
          }
        },
        "grid_item_L4KaaH": {
          "type": "grid-item",
          "settings": {
            "grid-item_image": "shopify://shop_images/tap-2.png",
            "grid-item_heading": "Direct to Tap",
            "grid-item_paragraph": "<p>You can also run micro tubing directly from a garden tap, though a pressure regulator may be needed to maintain steady flow. This works well for smaller setups without a full irrigation system.</p>",
            "grid-item_btn-label": "",
            "grid-item_btn-link": ""
          }
        },
        "grid_item_ajQC9y": {
          "type": "grid-item",
          "settings": {
            "grid-item_image": "shopify://shop_images/water-tank.png",
            "grid-item_heading": "Water Tanks",
            "grid-item_paragraph": "<p>Pods can operate from low-pressure sources like rain barrels. Ensure the tank is positioned above the pod so water flows by gravity for proper operation.</p>",
            "grid-item_btn-label": "",
            "grid-item_btn-link": ""
          }
        },
        "grid_item_Jk7HcQ": {
          "type": "grid-item",
          "settings": {
            "grid-item_image": "shopify://shop_images/centered-step-3.png",
            "grid-item_heading": "Step three",
            "grid-item_paragraph": "<p>Once connected, turn on the water supply and let the pod do the rest. Its automatic valve shuts off when full and allows refilling in under two minutes once pressure is restored.</p>",
            "grid-item_btn-label": "",
            "grid-item_btn-link": ""
          }
        },
        "grid_item_4NJnJV": {
          "type": "grid-item",
          "settings": {
            "grid-item_image": "shopify://shop_images/fertilizer.png",
            "grid-item_heading": "Fertiliser use",
            "grid-item_paragraph": "<p>You can use fully water-soluble fertiliser with the pod. Premix it in water, then flush with clean water after use to prevent clogs. Avoid non-water-soluble fertilisers, as they can block the system.</p>",
            "grid-item_btn-label": "",
